{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2b7-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1536"},"text":"§ 1536.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Surviving spouses of Spanish-American War veterans","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2b8-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary shall pay to the surviving spouse of each Spanish-American War veteran who met the service requirements of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1512/a"},"text":"section 1512(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" a pension at the monthly rate of $70, unless such surviving spouse was the spouse of the veteran during such veteran’s service in the Spanish-American War, in which case the monthly rate shall be $75."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2b9-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" If there is a child of the veteran, the rate of pension paid to the surviving spouse under subsection (a) shall be increased by $8.13 per month for each such child.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2ba-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" No pension shall be paid to a surviving spouse of a veteran under this section unless such surviving spouse was married to such veteran—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2bb-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1938-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1938","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2bc-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" for one year or more; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2bd-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" for any period of time if a child was born of the marriage, or was born to them before the marriage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2be-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2bf-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Any surviving spouse eligible for pension under this section shall, if such surviving spouse so elects, be paid pension at the rates prescribed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1541"},"text":"section 1541 of this title","children":[],"tail":", and under the conditions (other than the service requirements) applicable to pension paid under that section to surviving spouses of veterans of a period of war. If pension is paid pursuant to such an election, the election shall be irrevocable."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2c0-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s1536/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary shall pay each month to the surviving spouse of each Spanish-American War veteran who is receiving, or entitled to receive, pension based on a need of regular aid and attendance, whichever amount is greater (A) that which is payable to such surviving spouse under subsections (a) and (b) of this section as increased by section 544 ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002027"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002027"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1978","children":[],"tail":"; or (B) that which is payable under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1541"},"text":"section 1541 of this title","children":[],"tail":", as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1978","children":[],"tail":", as increased by such section 544,"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002027"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" as in effect on such date, to a surviving spouse of a World War I veteran with the same annual income and corpus of estate. Each change in the amount of pension required by this paragraph shall be effective as of the first day of the month during which the facts of the particular case warrant such change, and shall be made without specific application therefor."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc2c2e2c1-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/857"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–857","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1138"},"text":"72 Stat. 1138","children":[],"tail":", § 536; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/77/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–77, title I","children":[],"tail":", §§ 101(a), 105, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-08-31"},"text":"Aug. 31, 1967","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/81/178"},"text":"81 Stat. 178","children":[],"tail":", 179; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/328/tI/s107"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–328, title I, § 107","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/395"},"text":"86 Stat. 395","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/169/tI/s106/32"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–169, title I, § 106(32)","children":[],"tail":"–(37), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/1018"},"text":"89 Stat. 1018","children":[],"tail":", 1019; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/588/tI/s108"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–588, title I, § 108","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-04"},"text":"Nov. 4, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2502"},"text":"92 Stat. 2502","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 1536 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83","children":[],"tail":", §§ 4(b)(1), (2)(E), 5(a), (c)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-08-06"},"text":"Aug. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/404-406"},"text":"105 Stat. 404–406","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc2c2e2c2-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc2c2e2c3-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc2c2e2c4-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s544"},"text":"Section 544 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (d)(2), was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/588/tI/s112/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–588, title I, § 112(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-04"},"text":"Nov. 4, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2505"},"text":"92 Stat. 2505","children":[],"tail":", eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc2c2e2c5-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s536"},"text":"section 536 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “1512(a)” for “512(a)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s4/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 4(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(E), substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s5/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “1541” for “541” in pars. (1) and (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/83/s4/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–83, § 4(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(E), substituted “Secretary” for “Administrator”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/588/s108/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–588, § 108(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a period of war” for “World War I”, and struck out “, except as provided in paragraph (2)” after “irrevocable”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/588/s108/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–588, § 108(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1978","children":[],"tail":"” after “of this title” in two places, and “as in effect on such date” after “such section 544”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1975—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/169/s106/37"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–169, § 106(37)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Surviving spouses” for “Widows” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/169/s106/32"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–169, § 106(32)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “pay to the surviving spouse” for “pay to the widow”, “unless such surviving spouse” for “unless she”, “the spouse” for “the wife” and “such veteran’s” for “his”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/169/s106/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–169, § 106(33)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “surviving spouse” for “widow”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/169/s106/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–169, § 106(33)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “paid to a surviving spouse” for “paid to a widow”, “unless such surviving spouse” for “unless she” and “such veteran” for “him”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/169/s106/34"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–169, § 106(34)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Any surviving spouse” for “Any widow”, “if such surviving spouse” for “if she” and “surviving spouses” for “widows”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/169/s106/35"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–169, § 106(35)","children":[],"tail":", (36), substituted “surviving spouse” for “widow” wherever appearing, and “such surviving spouse” for “her”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1972—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/328"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–328","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1967—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/77/s105"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–77, § 105","children":[],"tail":", substituted “$70” for “$65”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/77/s101/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–77, § 101(a)","children":[],"tail":", qualified widow of a veteran for a pension by reducing in par. (2) the requisite marriage period from five years to one year and by making her eligible for benefits in par. (3) in event of antenuptial birth."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attri